cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.EC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of multi-item multi-bidder auctions, which is a classic topic in game theory and mechanism design. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the design of algorithms and approximation schemes, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The use of Bayesian optimization and the consideration of bidder valuations and distributions suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with revenue optimization, which is a key aspect of mechanism design, and therefore cs.EC (Economics and Computation) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of polynomial time approximation schemes suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category.
